2026-03-27T22:45:33.8448280Z             "body": "## Summary\r\n\r\n- Move the `dev` Docker image tag from dev-branch pushes to pull request builds\r\n- PR builds now receive both `dev` and `pr-<number>` tags\r\n- Main branch builds are unchanged (`latest` tag only, no `dev`)\r\n- Dev branch pushes fall through to generic branch tagging (still tagged `dev` via sanitized branch name)\r\n\r\n## Changes\r\n\r\n- `.github/workflows/build-and-test.yml` — Updated tag logic in both `docker` and `docker-admin` jobs: removed the explicit `dev` branch condition and added `dev` tag to the PR condition\r\n\r\n## Test Plan\r\n\r\n- [ ] Verify PR builds produce tags: `<sha>`, `latest-any`, `dev`, `pr-<number>`\r\n- [ ] Verify main branch builds produce tags: `<sha>`, `latest-any`, `latest`\r\n- [ ] Verify dev branch builds produce tags: `<sha>`, `latest-any`, `dev` (via branch name sanitization)\r\n- [ ] Verify other branch builds produce tags: `<sha>`, `latest-any`, `<branch-name>`",
